{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"bcd0ebfb-72e5-4796-93ce-6e073ff6087e","content":"No workflow files found in this directory, so here's the general guidance for switching to NuGet trusted publishing (OIDC):\n\n## Changes needed:\n\n**1. Register your package on nuget.org for trusted publishing:**\n- Go to nuget.org → Manage Package → Trusted Publishers\n- Add your GitHub repository (owner, repo, workflow file, optional environment)\n\n**2. Update your GitHub Actions workflow:**\n\n```yaml\njobs:\n  publish:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    permissions:\n      id-token: write  # Required for OIDC token request\n\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n\n      - uses: actions/setup-dotnet@v4\n        with:\n          dotnet-version: '8.x'\n\n      # Pack your project\n      - run: dotnet pack --configuration Release\n\n      # Push without an API key — uses OIDC\n      - name: Publish to NuGet\n        run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg\n          --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n**Key differences:**\n| Before (API key) | After (OIDC) |\n|---|---|\n| `secrets.NUGET_API_KEY` passed to `--api-key` | No `--api-key` needed |\n| No special permissions | `permissions: id-token: write` required |\n| Secret rotation needed | No secrets to manage |\n\n**3. Remove** the `NUGET_API_KEY` secret from your repo settings once verified.\n\n> **Note:** If you use a GitHub environment (e.g., `production`), specify it in both the workflow (`environment: production`) and the nuget.org trusted publisher config for tighter security.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"294e8f4f-135f-4e18-9ae3-9f706f9d79ef","outputTokens":410,"requestId":"101B:2E6F9:2A3AC10:2E88F00:69FD34AE"},"id":"0da49851-1733-477a-b384-399a02de49d0","timestamp":"2026-05-08T00:56:23.468Z","parentId":"5ce85d02-1fde-4421-b0fa-be6504264a6b"}
